cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of landmark detection in images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a method that involves learning to map an image of an object to an image of its landmarks, which can be seen as an image translation problem (cs.MM). The method is based on CycleGAN, which is a popular deep learning framework for image-to-image translation (cs.LG). The authors also introduce an analytical and differentiable renderer for the skeleton image, which involves some mathematical modeling (cs.GR). Finally, the method is unsupervised, meaning that it does not require labeled data, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
